                        li #[strong Special Abilities:] Each type of Dwarf has its own special abilities, listed in the corresponding entry.
                    //-
                        Lenses: Loyal, Pragmatic
                        Cog - Archives, Counters, Inventory (Math)
                            Tough as Nails; Dark Vision
                        Hulk - Warriors, Loyal to Society (Social Sciences)
                            Tough as Nails; Setback to Social
                        Knarr - Presentation, Perception, Deception (Lit/Art) - "The only thing that matters is what is seen."
                            Aristocrat; Setback to Social
                        Carrack - Extreme tinkerers with _everything_ (Science)
                            Intellectual; Dark Vision
                    h5.text-center Cog Dwarf
                    p Cog Dwarves are counters. They are archivists, quartermasters, accountants, and tabulators. Cog Dwarves are, even for dwarves, keen on first establishing the known facts. #[em What is] must be truly understood before #[em what might be] can be tackled. They are not myopic about inventory to the point of impracticality, but a lack of quantification of their own assets (both literal and abstract) will drive them mad.
                    p Two thousand years ago, the Cog Dwarves sold their homeworld to the Aven and joined the Hegemony. For what, nobody knows. But they have made themselves right at home in the Hegemony, with their nature to count at perfect match with the Aven's particular way of looking at property ownership.
                    p Cog Dwarves tend to be bronze in complexion, with hair ranging from red to brown to black. Unlike the Hulk Dwarves, the women don't have beards. Their eyes tend to brown or black, though a few are born with eyes like green emeralds, known as "emerald children".
                    p Cog Dwarves tend to favor adornments woven into their hair or worn as bracelets or brooches, because piercings and tattoos are seen as commitments, and a changing fashion should not be promised for life. Their clothes tend to be very functional, ready for their jobs at hand. Most situations involving 'nice clothes' are dealt with by adding a fair amount of jewelry to their newest or most expensive regular clothes.
                    ul 
                        li #[strong Starting Skills:] Cog Dwarves begin with one rank in Negotiation. You still cannot train their Negotiation above rank 2 during character creation.
                        li #[strong Dark Vision:] When making skill checks, Cog Dwarves remove up to #[span.dice.setback bb] imposed due to darkness.
                        li #[strong Tough as Nails:] Once per session, a Cog Dwarf may spend a Story Point as an out-of-turn incidental immediately after suffering a Critical Injury and determining the result. If they do so, they count the result rolled as “01.”
                    p #[strong Naming Conventions. ] Cog Dwarfs 
