                    h3#Elf.text-center Elf
                    p 
                        img.img-fluid.img-right-floater(src='./../content/images/species_elf.png')
                        | Elves are an ancient race, masters of ancient magic. They are the only species capable of traveling via The Ways, and their ability to exist in places of dangerous purity is unsurpassed. They are curious beings, driven by purpose but enabled by their long lives to take moments, sometimes years, to enjoy themselves and to reflect.
                    p All elves once originated on the lost planet of Avalon, though that was tens of thousands of years ago. The species of elves have since diverged, yet more than any other species, they have a respect for each other, no matter their culture or nationality.
                    p #[strong Physiology. ] Elves are exemplars of primal beauty. They are never ugly, merely #[em haunting] or #[em too beautiful], aesthetically compelling even to races wholly alien to Elves (like Vrar or Mind Flayers). They are a little shorter than Humans, between 4'10" and 6', and lighter, weighing between 100 and 160 pounds. Even without age-enhancement technology, Elves live between four and six hundred years. Elves exhibit even less sexual dimorphism than Humans, with the only differences being males weigh ever so slightly more, and females tend to live a few decades longer.
                    p #[strong Society. ] Elven society tends to value tradition above all else. Whether this is because they are #[em stuck in their ways] or #[em taking the long view] depends on who you ask. Held positions, whether appointed or elected, tend to be measured in decades. Projects are undertaken that may not see completion for a century, as a matter of course. Change is viewed as inevitable, but haste is viewed with suspicion.
                    h5.text-center Species Ability
